# NestJS conventions

## Module layout (feature-first)
```
src/
  programs/        # program capacity aggregate: limit, reserved, available, base currency, version
  reservations/    # reservation + release lifecycle, the atomic capacity operations
  ledger/          # append-only capacity movements (source of truth for derived totals)
  treasury/        # kafka consumer: deltas + reconciliation snapshots
  fx/              # currency conversion (rate source + rounding policy)
  idempotency/     # dedupe store + guard/interceptor
  auth/            # authentication for all endpoints
  common/          # money value object, decimal utils, filters, interceptors, correlation id
  config/          # validated config schema
```

## Controllers
- Thin. Validate via DTO, delegate to a service, map result to a response DTO. No DB access, no math.
- Mutating endpoints require `Idempotency-Key` header (documented, enforced by guard).
- Return explicit response DTOs — never leak entities.

## DTOs
- `class-validator` + `class-transformer`. Enable `whitelist` + `forbidNonWhitelisted` globally.
- Money in requests: `{ amount: string /* minor units, integer */, currency: string /* ISO 4217 */ }`.
  Accept amount as string to avoid JS number precision loss on the wire; validate it parses to a positive integer.
- Never accept a raw float amount. Reject it in validation.

## REST surface (suggested)
- `POST /programs/:id/reservations`      -> create reservation (consumes capacity)
- `POST /reservations/:id/release`       -> release (returns capacity)
- `GET  /programs/:id/availability`      -> current total / reserved / available (+ currency, version)
- All under an authenticated guard. No anonymous access to any route.

## Services
- Own the transaction boundary. One business operation = one DB transaction.
- Inject a repository/data layer; do not build SQL strings inline except for the atomic capacity update.
- Throw typed domain exceptions (e.g. `InsufficientCapacityError`, `CurrencyMismatchError`,
  `StaleSnapshotError`, `DuplicateOperationError`).
